Former Boks team manager Arthob Petersen. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Former Boks team manager Arthob Petersen died on Tuesday due to COVID-19 related illness. Petersen, who hailed from Paarl in the Western Cape, served rugby in various capacities for 40-years. READ: Theatre legend Dawn Lindberg dies aged 75 His most notable role was team manager under the leadership of Carel du Plessis and Nick Mallett during 1997 and 1999. He was also in charge of the team with former coach Jake White at the helm and was again involved between 2008 and 2009 with ex-mentor Peter de Villiers. He also served the game as chairman and coach of the Lower Paarl Rugby Club after beginning his administrative career as chairman of the South Cape Teachers’ Training College club.